# 🌸 Çiçeksepeti Competitive Price Monitor

An automated competitive intelligence pipeline that tracks real-time pricing across Çiçeksepeti and rival platforms — delivering instant Slack alerts when price changes are detected.

Built as a personal analytics engineering project to demonstrate end-to-end pipeline design: data ingestion, change detection, alerting, and historical storage.

---

## 🏗️ Architecture

```
Rival websites (30 products)
        ↓
Puppeteer scraper (Cloudflare bypass)
        ↓
Price change detection engine
        ↓
Slack alert  ──────────────  BigQuery (historical storage)
```

---

## ✨ Features

- **30 products monitored** across Çiçeksepeti and competitors
- **Automated price change detection** — compares current vs. previous prices
- **Slack alerts** — instant notifications with product, old price, new price, and % change
- **BigQuery sync** — all price snapshots written to BigQuery for historical trend analysis
- **Looker Studio dashboard** — visual benchmarking of pricing trends over time
- **GitHub Actions scheduler** — runs automatically 4x daily (10:00, 12:00, 15:00, 18:00 TR time), no server needed
- **Cloudflare bypass** — reliable scraping via Puppeteer with anti-bot handling
- **Test mode** — simulate price changes locally without affecting production data

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

| Layer | Tool |
|-------|------|
| Scraping | Node.js + Puppeteer |
| Orchestration | GitHub Actions |
| Storage | BigQuery (GCP) |
| Alerting | Slack Webhooks |
| Visualization | Looker Studio |
| Language | JavaScript (scraper) + Python (BigQuery sync) |

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
├── .github/workflows/
│   └── price-monitor.yml       # GitHub Actions workflow (4x daily schedule)
├── scraper.js                  # Puppeteer scraper with Cloudflare bypass
├── price_monitor_github.js     # Main orchestration script
├── bigquery_sync.py            # Writes price snapshots to BigQuery
├── benchmarking_dashboard.py   # Price trend analysis
├── price_history.json          # Local price state (change detection)
└── package.json                # Node.js dependencies
```

---

## 🚀 Setup

### 1. Clone & install dependencies
```bash
git clone https://github.com/hasansavli-tc17/ciceksepeti-price-monitor.git
cd ciceksepeti-price-monitor
npm install
```

### 2. Configure GitHub Secrets
Go to **Repository Settings → Secrets → Actions** and add:

| Secret | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL` | Your Slack incoming webhook URL |

### 3. Run manually (optional)
```bash
# Live run
SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL=your_webhook node price_monitor_github.js

# Test mode (simulates a price change)
TEST_MODE=true SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL=your_webhook node price_monitor_github.js
```

The GitHub Actions workflow runs automatically on schedule — no manual intervention needed.

---

## 📊 Output

**Slack alert example:**
> 🔴 Price change detected — Rose Bouquet (50cm)
> Çiçeksepeti: ~~₺349~~ → **₺299** (-14.3%)

**BigQuery table:** All price snapshots stored with timestamp, product, platform, and price for longitudinal trend analysis.

**Looker Studio dashboard:** Visual benchmarking of price movements across platforms over time.

---

## 🔒 Security

- Slack webhook URL stored in GitHub Secrets — never hardcoded
- No credentials in codebase

---

## 💡 Why I Built This

Competitive pricing is one of the highest-leverage data problems in e-commerce. This project started as an internal tool to give the Çiçeksepeti team faster visibility into competitor pricing — and evolved into a fully automated pipeline running in production.

